      "amount": "1 tsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Grease a 9x9-inch baking dish with the unsalted butter.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the free-range eggs, heavy cream, salt, and lemon juice until well combined.",
    "Stir in the grated Emmental cheese, crushed almond flour, chopped onion, diced smoked sausage, chopped bell pepper, fresh dill, and lemon zest.",
    "Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish and spread it evenly.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the eggs are set.",
    "Let the bake cool for 5 minutes before slicing.",
    "Serve warm, optionally garnished with extra fresh dill."
  ],
